  "prompt": "Does all the questions get answered in Quora?",
  "response": "No, not all questions on Quora get answered. Several factors contribute to this:\n\n*   **Lack of Expertise:** Sometimes, a question might be very niche or require specific knowledge that no one on Quora has or is willing to share.\n*   **Low Visibility:** Some questions might not be seen by enough users who have the relevant expertise.\n*   **Poor Question Quality:** Questions that are unclear, poorly written, or overly broad may be ignored.\n*   **Lack of Interest:** Some questions may simply not be interesting enough to attract answers, even if people have the knowledge.\n*   **Time Since Asked:** Older questions are less likely to be answered, as they are further down the feed.\n*   **Policy Violation:** Questions that violate Quora's policies (e.g., hate speech, spam) are removed and won't get answered.\n*   **Duplication:** If a question is very similar to existing questions with many answers, people might not bother answering it again.\n\nWhile Quora has a large user base and aims to provide answers to as many questions as possible, it's not guaranteed that every question will receive a response.",
